An Azure subscription is a logical container used to provision and manage Azure resources. It acts as a boundary for billing, access control, and resource management.

Each subscription is linked to an Azure account and can contain multiple resource groups and resources.

For example, a company may have separate subscriptions for different departments such as IT, finance, and development.

A real-life use case is cost management. By separating subscriptions, organizations can track spending for each department independently.

Another example is access control. Different teams can be granted permissions at the subscription level to ensure security and proper governance.

Subscriptions are essential for organizing resources and managing costs effectively in Azure.
